      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 2-year-old child with respiratory distress is brought in for evaluation. The history reveals an autosomal recessive condition causing recurrent respiratory and gastrointestinal symptoms. Radiological findings include bronchiectasis, leading to a diagnosis of Cystic Fibrosis (CF). Which genetic mutation is responsible, and what is the most common cause of pneumonia in this child?</span></span></span></p>",
