      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 2-month-old premature infant with a history of chronic lung disease is brought to the emergency department with tachypnea, retractions, and an oxygen saturation of 88%. The infant was born at 33 weeks gestation and requires oxygen support at home. The respiratory viral panel returns positive for Respiratory Syncytial Virus (RSV). Which of the following statements about RSV infection is NOT true?</span></span></span></p>",
