      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 3-month-old infant with a history of recurrent respiratory infections and a diagnosis of Cystic Fibrosis presents with bulging of the anterior fontanelle, fussiness, refusal to feed, and vomiting. The infant does not have a fever, and a CT scan of the head shows no signs of trauma or tumor. Based on the history and current presentation, what is the suspected condition?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q3640068",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
